The paper deals with the use of time reversal and All-Rake transceivers in multiple access communications, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance analysis of these techniques in terms of symbol error probability and spectral efficiency, which are metrics commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of channel estimation procedures, which is a topic related to communication systems (cs.COM).
